  "prompt": "How widely accepted are credit cards at small businesses and restaurants in Barbados?",
  "response": "In Barbados, credit cards are generally accepted at many businesses, including larger establishments, restaurants, hotels, and popular tourist destinations. However, smaller businesses or more remote locations might prefer cash or local payment methods. While credit card acceptance is fairly common, it\u2019s advisable to carry some cash for situations where credit cards might not be accepted or for smaller purchases. It's always a good idea to check with individual businesses if you are unsure about their payment methods.",
